{"article_id":"nsDNwH6AbFdKAMGm","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"US policy toward Saudi Arabia has run into serious trouble .","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"There is mounting evidence","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"that a prominent Saudi journalist , Jamal Khashoggi , was murdered in Turkey by a Saudi hit squad .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The Trump administration ' s reaction to the case was criticized as being delayed ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"but the allegations have spawned a bipartisan call from Congress","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"for sanctions to be imposed on Saudi Arabia","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"if it turns out Mr. Khashoggi was indeed killed by Saudi operatives .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"President Trump \" has a longstanding position","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"that he doesn ' t care very much about internal affairs","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"- ' How you run your country is up to you ' is how he likes to put it -","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"so I would assume","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"that would be his impulse in this case , \"","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"says Patrick Clawson , an expert in US-Saudi relations .","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"Others say","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"what is already known about Khashoggi ' s disappearance is enough","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"to trigger some action .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"\" I can ' t imagine","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"the outcome is going to be no change , \"","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"says Jon Alterman of the Center for Strategic and International Studies in Washington .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"\" But the outcome is not going to be the US ending its close relationship with Saudi Arabia , \" either ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"he adds .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"\" It will be a calibrated approach","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that will be criticized as inadequate by some people . \"","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Ever since President Trump accepted the counsel of son-in-law and Middle East adviser Jared Kushner","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"to make Saudi Arabia the first foreign trip of his presidency ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"it was clear that the kingdom was to be the linchpin of his administration ' s regional policy .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"From countering Iran","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"and achieving Israeli-Palestinian peace","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to promoting sustainable reforms of rigid Arab societies ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"Saudi Arabia under its young crown prince","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"( and de facto leader )","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Mohammed bin Salman would be Washington ' s go-to partner in the region .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"Now the Saudi strategy","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"Mr. Kushner engineered","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"has been rattled","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"and indeed threatens to come crashing down .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"The reason ?","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"The stunning allegations","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"- which","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"Mr. Trump this week hinted","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"are likely more fact than accusation -","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"that a prominent Saudi journalist and US resident , Jamal Khashoggi , was murdered in Turkey by a Saudi government hit squad","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"dispatched by the crown prince .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Mr. Khashoggi ' s disappearance Oct. 2 while with Saudi officials in Turkey has prompted little in the way","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"of clarifying information from the Saudis .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"But it has spawned vociferous reaction from rights groups and a bipartisan call from Congress for answers","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"- and for sanctions to be imposed on Saudi Arabia","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"if it turns out Khashoggi was indeed killed by Saudi operatives .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Trump , too , has expressed his disapproval of Khashoggi ' s disappearance","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"- although it took the White House more than a week to comment on the case .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"That delay , as well as the president ' s stated reluctance","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"to take punitive action ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"suggests to some regional analysts","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"that any rough period ahead for US-Saudi relations could be short-lived .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"\" This president has a longstanding position","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"that he doesn ' t care very much about internal affairs","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"' How you run your country is up to you ' is how he likes to put it -","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"so I would assume","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"that would be his impulse in this case , \"","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"says Patrick Clawson , an expert in US-Saudi relations at the Washington Institute for Near East Policy .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"\" Reflecting that ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"the US position toward the Saudis is going to be that ' This","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"[ the Khashoggi affair ]","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"is not good for your interests , ' \"","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"Mr. Clawson adds .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"\" It ' s not going to be that this is a moral outrage","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"that calls into question our relations","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"or that outweighs our common interests . \"","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"Others say","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"the facts of the case will determine the US response ,","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"but that what is already known about Khashoggi ' s disappearance is enough","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"to trigger some action .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"\" I can ' t imagine","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"the outcome is going to be no change ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"based on the unrefuted pattern of facts \"","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"already established ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"says Jon Alterman , director of the Middle East Program at the Center for Strategic and International Studies","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"( CSIS )","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"in Washington and a former special assistant to the State Department ' s Bureau of Near Eastern Affairs .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"\" But the outcome is not going to be the US ending its close relationship with Saudi Arabia , \" either ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"he adds .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"\" It will be a calibrated approach","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"that will be criticized as inadequate by some people . \"","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Kashoggi ' s last verified whereabouts was the Saudi consulate in Istanbul ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"where his fiancée says","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"he made an appointment","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"to get documents for their upcoming wedding .","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"Saudi officials insist","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Khashoggi left the consulate after his appointment","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"and that they do not know","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"where he is .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"But Turkish officials assert","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"he was killed in the consulate by a hit squad of 15 agents","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"dispatched from Riyadh ,","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"his body dismembered","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"and transported to Saudi Arabia .","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"On Thursday , Turkish officials claimed to have audio and video tapes of Kashoggi ' s interrogation , torture , and murder in the consulate .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"US intelligence officials confirm","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"that over recent weeks they had picked up chatter among Saudi officials","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"discussing a plan","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"to lure Khashoggi back to Saudi Arabia","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"and then to detain him ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"as first reported by the Washington Post .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"That information raised questions","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"about whether Khashoggi was informed of the plan","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"concerning him","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"- US intelligence agencies operate under a \" duty","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"to warn \" individuals of such intercepted plots ,","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"even if the individual is not an American citizen .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"Khashoggi , a Washington Post columnist , was no radical anti-regime dissident","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"but rather a Saudi insider","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"who gradually soured on the royal court","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"- and in particular on the crown prince .","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"And senior Trump administration officials have lent credence to the darkest conjectures about Khashoggi .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"The White House announced this week","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"that Kushner , national security adviser John Bolton , and Secretary of State Mike Pompeo each called Crown Prince Mohammed","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"and implored the kingdom to come clean","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"- officially \" be transparent \" -","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"about Khashoggi ' s fate .","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"And then there was Trump ' s assertion Wednesday to Fox News","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"that ,","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"while he did not like where the evidence appeared to be pointing","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"concerning Khashoggi ,","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"he also did not foresee taking actions","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"- such as cutting off arm sales to Saudi Arabia -","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"that would hurt US industry and jobs .","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"At the same time , some regional analysts say","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"the Khashoggi affair can ' t help but cast doubt on US relations with Saudi Arabia","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"- in particular concerning the kingdom ' s role in the Trump White House ' s plan","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"for countering Iranian adventurism and malign activities -","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"including ruthless repression of political dissidents at home and abroad .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"If Saudi Arabia is increasingly seen to be following the Iranian playbook ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"they say","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"- mounting elaborate missions","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"to silence journalists and dissidents","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"by jailing or even killing them ,","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"and wreaking havoc across the region ,","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"as exemplified by the disastrous Saudi-led war in Yemen -","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"it ' s going to be increasingly difficult for the White House to follow its Saudi strategy .","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"Congressional pressure","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"to hold Saudi Arabia accountable in meaningful ways","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"intensified all week .","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"\" Any message from Congress","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"that support is being threatened","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"has a deep effect on the kingdom","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"- and that message is being sent every day , \"","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"says Mr. Alterman at CSIS .","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"On Wednesday , the Senate Foreign Relations Committee sent Trump a letter formally requesting the White House conduct an investigation under the Global Magnitsky Human Rights Accountability Act .","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"The act was first passed in response to Russia ' s jailing and death","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"while in custody of anti-corruption activist Sergei Magnitsky in 2009 .","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"It calls on the president to conduct an investigation into a case of state-sponsored human rights violations","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"and to report back to the Senate committee with findings and a determination","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"of whether sanctions should be imposed .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"Recourse to the Magnitsky Act is a \" pretty strong step , \"","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"Foreign Relations Committee Chairman Bob Corker","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"( R )","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"of Tennessee said Thursday","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"that any determination of a Saudi role in Khashoggi ' s disappearance would put the administration under \" immense pressure \"","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"to follow through with action , such as sanctions .","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"Other senators are going further ,","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"suggesting","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"that arms sales to Saudi Arabia should be halted","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"if it is determined the Saudi state killed Khashoggi .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"Calling for a \" fundamental break in our relationship with Saudi Arabia \"","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"if an investigation reveals","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"that a \" US resident \" was \" murdered \" by Saudi officials ,","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"Sen. Chris Murphy","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"( D )","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"of Connecticut said","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"cutting off arms sales would be an obvious step .","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"\" The United States can not be in a military partnership with a country","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"that has this little concern for human life , \"","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"Other senators acknowledge","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"that Saudi Arabia is likely to remain a strategic partner of the US under almost any scenario ,","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"but they insist","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"that after Khashoggi it can ' t be business as usual .","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"Regional analysts","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"who have been supportive of close US-Saudi relations , and in particular of the two powers ' efforts","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"to counter Iran ,","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"lament","depth":9},{"id":182,"text":"that the Khashoggi case will likely act as something of a last straw","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"that tips relations , perhaps back to the days of tensions","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"experienced during the Obama administration .","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"Crown Prince Mohammed ,","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"familiarly known as MBS ,","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"is on the brink of shifting in US perceptions from \" reformer \" to \" rogue , \"","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"says Elliott Abrams , a former US diplomat and National Security Council Middle East director","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"who is now at the Council on Foreign Relations .","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"Indeed over the past year MBS ,","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"hailed in some circles for allowing Saudi women to drive","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"and for anticorruption initiatives against some Saudi high and mighty ,","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"has also ordered a string of blatant extraterritorial exercises of power","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"that went largely unchallenged","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"and that","depth":15},{"id":196,"text":"experts say","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"may have led the prince to conclude","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"that his crackdowns on regime critics had Washington ' s tacit approval .","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"MBS has detained thousands of rights and reform activists .","depth":9},{"id":200,"text":"Last March , in a move","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"that some say","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"presaged the Saudi state ' s Khashoggi mission ,","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"a Saudi women ' s rights activist was nabbed in Abu Dhabi","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"and whisked back to Saudi Arabia","depth":13},{"id":205,"text":"where she was jailed .","depth":13},{"id":206,"text":"And in a bizarre caper last November , Saudi officials detained Lebanese Prime Minister Saad Hariri","depth":13},{"id":207,"text":"while on a visit to the kingdom","depth":13},{"id":208,"text":"- even ordering him to go on TV","depth":14},{"id":209,"text":"and announce his resignation .","depth":14},{"id":210,"text":"( He is still in office . )","depth":13},{"id":211,"text":"More recently , Saudi Arabia in August cut trade ties with Canada ,","depth":12},{"id":212,"text":"ordered all Saudi students in Canada to return home ,","depth":14},{"id":213,"text":"and expelled the Canadian ambassador to Riyadh","depth":14},{"id":214,"text":"after the Canadian Embassy issued a tweet","depth":14},{"id":215,"text":"calling for the release of jailed women ' s rights activists .","depth":14},{"id":216,"text":"Saying","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"the Canadian episode showcased MBS as an \" impetuous leader","depth":11},{"id":218,"text":"who tends to act first","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"and think later , \"","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"the Washington Institute ' s Clawson says","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"he expects the White House to have harsh words for the Saudi leadership over Khashoggi","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"- but ,","depth":13},{"id":223,"text":"as Trump has already indicated ,","depth":14},{"id":224,"text":"not to fundamentally disrupt relations","depth":14},{"id":225,"text":"if the White House can avoid it .","depth":12},{"id":226,"text":"Alterman of CSIS says","depth":10},{"id":227,"text":"the one thing","depth":12},{"id":228,"text":"that might prompt a rethinking by the crown prince","depth":12},{"id":229,"text":"is a sense","depth":13},{"id":230,"text":"growing in the kingdom","depth":13},{"id":231,"text":"that his actions have gone on to the point","depth":13},{"id":232,"text":"of undermining US-Saudi relations .","depth":13},{"id":233,"text":"\" There ' s no question that the most significant accomplishment","depth":12},{"id":234,"text":"Mohammed bin Salman has","depth":12},{"id":235,"text":"is revitalizing the US-Saudi relationship , \"","depth":11},{"id":236,"text":"says Alterman ,","depth":11},{"id":237,"text":"who notes","depth":12},{"id":238,"text":"that there was a sense","depth":14},{"id":239,"text":"that the strategic partnership was \" slipping away \" under President Barack Obama ,","depth":14},{"id":240,"text":"presenting a \" profound challenge to the security of the kingdom . \"","depth":13},{"id":241,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":242,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":243,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":244,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":245,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":246,"text":"What that means , in his view , is that US actions in response to the Khashoggi affair","depth":5},{"id":247,"text":"\" intended to somehow change the Saudis ' behavior \"","depth":5},{"id":248,"text":"will have an impact , \" more profoundly on the crown prince than on anything else . \" The question will be \" how much anything","depth":6},{"id":249,"text":"the US does will change Saudi behavior , \"","depth":6},{"id":250,"text":"he says ,","depth":5},{"id":251,"text":"\" and that remains very unclear . \"","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":503,"left":492,"right":502,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":492,"left":274,"right":491,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":258,"right":273,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":0,"right":257,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":253,"right":256,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":253,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":3,"right":255,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":255,"left":4,"right":254,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":263,"right":272,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":263,"left":262,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":260,"right":261,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":260,"left":259,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":272,"left":265,"right":271,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":13,"right":264,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":264,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":267,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":266,"right":18,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":266,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":270,"left":268,"right":269,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":268,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":491,"left":334,"right":490,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":334,"left":319,"right":333,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":319,"left":282,"right":318,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":282,"left":276,"right":281,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":275,"right":25,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":275,"left":23,"right":24,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":278,"right":280,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":278,"left":26,"right":277,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":280,"left":279,"right":31,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":279,"left":29,"right":30,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":318,"left":292,"right":317,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":285,"right":291,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":284,"right":35,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":284,"left":283,"right":34,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":283,"left":32,"right":33,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":36,"right":290,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":290,"left":288,"right":289,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":288,"left":37,"right":287,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":286,"right":40,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":286,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":41,"right":42,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":317,"left":302,"right":316,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":296,"right":301,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":296,"left":293,"right":295,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":293,"left":43,"right":44,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":294,"right":47,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":45,"right":46,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":301,"left":297,"right":300,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":48,"right":49,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":298,"right":299,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":52,"right":53,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"